The defendant Mystykal D Manns was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Attempt Attempt Solicitation of Prostitutes, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 944.32.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

ORDER TO PRODUCE, FILED AND SIGNED. kl

Sentencing hearing proceeded. Statements made as to sentencing.  

As to COUNT 1 as AMENDED:
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 36 MONTHS, concurrent with case 14CF3557; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 18 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 18 MONTHS.  

Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program. The defendant is NOTeligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

Court ordered the conditions of extended supervision be the same as the conditions ordered in case 14CF3557:

1) No contact with the victims C.I., J.J.M., or the co-defendant Anthony Powell; 
2) Defendant is prohibited from maintaining any social media accounts.
3) Any electronic devices must be turned over to agent for inspection upon demand.
4) No possession or use of controlled substances.  
5) Submit to random drug screens.

Court WAIVED all costs, fees and surcharges (including the DNA surcharge) as this is part of a continuous event.

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
Filed;
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
signed Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgement.

Plea hearing proceeded. Defendant sworn in:

As to COUNT 1 as AMENDED-
Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the defendant guilty.  Judgment of conviction entered.
  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon she may never possess any gun or other firearms. 
Court advised defendant that her voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until her civil rights are restored.  

Court advised defendant if she is not a citizen of the United States of America, that upon a plea of guilty or no contest for this offense, she could be deported, excluded from admission to her country, or denied naturalization under federal law.  
Court advised that the defendant will have to provide a DNA sample, to the Wisconsin State Crime Laboratory for DNA testing and pay a DNA surcharge.
